<div id="business2" class="format2 scrollbar">
 <ul>
  <li> <a href="http://www.ebizguides.com/">eBizguides.com</a> - Provide business travellers with general commercial and financial  	information on the main sectors of various African countries. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.mbendi.com/">MBendi: Information for  	Africa</a> - African business and financial news portal also  	provides a business directory with free listings organized by  	country and business sector, and information on industries,  	employment and opportunities. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
  <li> <a href="http://travel.independent.co.uk/africa/">The  	Independent - Travel: Africa</a> - African short break and holiday  	news and information from the travel section of the newspaper. UK. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.latimes.com/travel/la-tr-destinationafricagallery,1,5337679.storygallery">Los  	Angeles Times - Travel Destinations: Africa</a> - Travel columns  	about vacations and safaris in African countries. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://travel.nytimes.com/travel/guides/africa/overview.html">New  	York Times - Travel: Africa</a> - Articles and multimedia on African  	countries and cities from the newspaper's travel section. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.travelafricamag.com/">Travel Africa  	Magazine</a> - A specialist magazine covering a spectrum of topics  	including wildlife, culture, history and conservation. </li>
</ul>
Africa news
<ul>
  <li> <a href="http://mathaba.net/africa2020/">Africa2020</a> - Offers daily reports and commentaries from around the states of  	the African Union. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.africatower.com/">Africa  	Tower</a> - African portal providing weather, news, sports, current  	events, travel and business information. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://afraf.oxfordjournals.org/">African  	Affairs</a> - Publishing articles on recent political, social and  	economic developments in sub-Saharan countries, including historical  	studies that illuminate current events in the continent. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.africast.tv/">Africast</a> - Offers the sights, sounds, storytelling and traditions of Africa  	via subscription video on demand (SVOD). </li>
  <li> <a href="http://members.lycos.co.uk/afrique2000/">Afrique  	Horizon</a> - Bi-monthly printed magazine covering all aspects of  	African music, politics, culture and society. In French and English. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.afrol.com/">Afrol</a> - News reports categorized by country, updated daily. [English,  	Spanish] </li>
   <li> <a href="http://www.america.gov/world/africa.html">America.Gov  	- Africa</a> - Press releases and transcripts from the U.S.  	Department of State.[various languages] </li>
  <li> <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/">BBC  	News - Africa</a> - In-depth African news, analysis and information  	with audio, video, forums, photo journals and country profiles. UK. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/africa/features/focus_magazine/">BBC  	World Service - Focus On Africa</a> - Quarterly magazine covers the  	latest political, economic, social, cultural and sporting  	developments in Africa. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.csmonitor.com/world/africa.html">Christian  	Science Monitor: Africa</a> - News and commentary featuring hopeful  	developments as well as disasters. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.cnn.com/CNNI/Programs/insideafrica/">CNN  	- Inside Africa</a> - Half-hour current affairs weekly program which  	provides global viewers with an inside look at political, economic,  	social and cultural affairs and trends in Africa. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.economist.com/world/africa/">The  	Economist - Africa</a> - Covers current politics, business,  	economics, finance and cultural trends in Africa. UK. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/">The  	Independent - World: Africa</a> - News, analysis and commentary  	about Africa-related news stories. UK. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.irinnews.org/IRIN-Africa.aspx">IRIN  	- Africa</a> - Integrated Regional Information Networks reports,  	categorized by topic and country. UN. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3036014/">MSNBC  	- World News: Africa</a> - Provides news stories, slide shows, video  	and fact files including coverage by Newsweek. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.africasia.com/newafrican/">New  	African</a> - Oldest Pan-African monthly in English covers  	political, economic and cultural developments. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/world/africa/">New  	York Times - International: Africa</a> - Current news and features  	from NYT journalists, breaking news from Reuters and AP, weather and  	readers' opinions. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.panapress.com/">Panapress</a> - Pan-African news agency provides news, analyses and roundups of  	events in and about Africa. [Arabic, English, French, Portuguese] </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.pbs.org/newshour/region/africa/">PBS  	- NewsHour: Africa</a> - Background reports about Africa include  	transcripts and pictures. USA. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://blogs.reuters.com/africanews/">Reuters  	- Africa Blog</a> - Group blog covering African business, politics  	and lifestyle, indexed by date, topic and contributor. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.topix.com/world/africa">Topix  	- Africa News</a> - News about Africa collected from various media  	sources on the web. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://radiostationworld.com/locations/africa/">TvRadioWorld  	- Africa</a> - List of broadcasters, TV and radio stations (local,  	national, international, shortwave and on the web), with links where  	available. Includes organizations, services and industry news. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.usafricaonline.com/">USAfrica  	Online</a> - News and opinion focussing on Africa-USA relations. </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/world/africa/index.html">Washington  	Post - World: Africa</a> - News, commentary, editorials and special  	reports about Africa along with coverage of each country  	individually. USA. [free reg.] </li>
    <li> <a href="http://wnafrica.com/">WorldNews Network - Africa</a> - Provides tagged headline links from worldwide media source,  	organized by topic and country. </li>
</ul>
</div>
